# No Em Dashes

Never use em dashes (Unicode U+2014, the character that looks like a long dash).

Replace them with commas, colons, or parentheses.

Use only standard keyboard punctuation in:
- Agent replies
- Docs and README
- UI copy
- Code comments
- Commit messages

Wrong: "Use Chroma — it is local."
Right: "Use Chroma: it is local."
Right: "Use Chroma (it is local)."
Right: "Use Chroma, it is local."
